      "FacilityID": 50334,
      "SummaryText": "This facility is operated by the City of Angleton, Texas Department of Utilities.  It is located at 500 Sebesta Road, Angleton, Brazoria County, Texas.  The facility has the potential to contain 2500 pounds or more of chlorine.  The amount of chlorine on site is normally 4000 pounds.  This plan contains a Worst Case Scenario and Alternative Release Scenario as required by regulation.\nThe plant is located in an Urban environment, with the worst case exposure of 1.3 miles.  Within that radius lies residences, an elementary school and a middle school, along with additional commercial locations.  The City Department of Utilities coordinates emergency response with the Angleton Fire Department, which serves as the City's expert on public notification, spill control and emergency response during a spill of any hazardous substance.\nThe has initiated a compliance review response plan which includes chlorine tank repair B kit for use by trained Fire Department personnel, an update to the required standard operations manual, and new training and fiting for PPE.  At the completion of this response (12/31/2006) all known deficiencies in the City's RMP will be cured."
    }
